ment -> deep-improvement rename surface. Results must be actionable/remediable.\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deltas/iter-001...\n  Line 10: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128167267,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18818240dffewuwJIHs587dTcP\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"call_02_6QFqWbeOiSGr3tOjgZTy8237\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"INTENT_SIGNALS|RESOURCE_MAP|smart router|smart.routing\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement\"},\"output\":\"Found 11 matches\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.9.0.0.md:\\n  Line 46: - **The skill doc presents Lane A and Lane B as parallel sections** instead of modes 1 to 3 plus a trailing Mode 4. A WHEN TO USE two-lane table was added, and the smart router gained a `MODEL_BENCHMARK` intent at weight 5 with a matching RESOURCE_MAP entry. DQI stayed in the excellent band at 97.\\n\\n  Line 50: - **`references/` and `assets/` are now organized by lane** (`agent-improvement/`, `model-benchmark/`, `shared/`) rather than by function. This supersedes the v1.8.0.0 function grouping (scoring, promotion-gates, integration, workflow), which was an intermediate step. Every literal was repointed: SKILL.md RESOURCE_MAP, DEFAULT_RESOURCE, RUNTIME_ASSETS, both lanes of command YAMLs, both command docs, README, graph-metadata, scripts, the feature catalog and playbook, and the benchmark profile's internal fixtureDir.\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:\\n  Line 87: **Lane awareness**: resources are organized by lane. `references/agent-improvement/` and `assets/agent-improvement/` carry Lane A guidance, while `references/model-benchmark/` and `assets/model-benchmark/` carry Lane B guidance. `RESOURCE_MAP` routes the `MODEL_BENCHMARK` intent to the Lane B references, and `RUNTIME_ASSETS` loads the Lane B benchmark profile only when the `MODEL_BENCHMARK` intent is selected. The `ALWAYS` and shared `references/shared/` resources apply...\n  Line 13: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128175150,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18818240dffewuwJIHs587dTcP\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_00_TwCfLA7bY3vECMIOq6lW0869\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deep-research-strategy.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # Deep Research Strategy — 122/001 skill-benchmark (run: MiniMax-2.7)\\n2: \\n3: ## 2. TOPIC\\n4: Design Lane C (\\\"skill-benchmark\\\") for the `deep-improvement` skill: how to benchmark whether a *skill* is well-structured, well-routed, efficient, and useful **in practice** (how AIs actually discover/use it), distinct from manual testing playbooks and sk-doc doc-shape validation. Plus the `deep-agent-improvement` → `deep-improvement` rename impact map.\\n5: \\n6: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\\n7: - [ ] RQ1: Scoring dimensions + weights for benchmarking real-world skill utilization (routing/activation accuracy, unprompted reference/asset discovery, efficiency, usefulness/ablation, structural connectivity); normalization across skills of different shapes.\\n8: - [ ] RQ2: A credible hint-free dispatch harness that captures which references/assets an AI loads + tool trace, without leaking the expected answer.\\n9: - [ ] RQ3: Score activation vs the skill-advisor, vs the in-SKILL.md smart router, or both as separate sub-scores; operational meaning of \\\"properly utilized\\\".\\n10: - [ ] RQ4: Scenario/fixture authoring — hand-authored vs generated-from-the-skill's-own-triggers; avoiding circularity.\\n11: - [ ] RQ5: How the Skill Benchmark Report should rank bottlenecks + e...\n  Line 14: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128175970,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18818240dffewuwJIHs587dTcP\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_01_qFwsMzx9cMqHvT6I2aOF8576\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: \\\"Phase 002: Rename deep-agent-improvement to deep-improvement\\\"\\n3: description: \\\"Rename the deep-agent-improvement skill to deep-improvement across skill dir, SKILL.md, commands, agent + runtime mirrors, advisor graph, descriptions.json, and cross-references; zero dangling refs; green advisor rebuild.\\\"\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"deep-improvement rename\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"122 phase 002\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"rename deep-agent-improvement\\\"\\n8: importance_tier: \\\"important\\\"\\n9: contextType: \\\"implementation\\\"\\n10: _memory:\\n11:   continuity:\\n12:     packet_pointer: \\\"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement\\\"\\n13:     last_updated_at: \\\"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\\\"\\n14:     last_updated_by: \\\"claude-opus\\\"\\n