ors (.claude/.codex/.gemini agents), skill-advisor graph (skill-graph.json), descriptions.json, sentinel sk-prompt-small-model, root CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md, internal self-references. Identify dangling-reference risks.\";;\n\n  Line 26: RESEARCH TOPIC: Design Lane C (\"skill-benchmark\") for the deep-improvement skill — benchmark whether a SKILL is well-structured, well-routed, efficient, and useful IN PRACTICE (how AIs actually discover and use it at the right moments), distinct from manual testing playbooks and from sk-doc doc-shape validation. Also map the deep-agent-improvement -> deep-improvement rename surface. Results must be actionable/remediable.\n\n  Line 31: - .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md  (target skill: Lane A agent-improvement + Lane B model-benchmark; smart router INTENT_SIGNALS/RESOURCE_MAP; three pluggable seams candidate-source/dispatcher/scorer; loop-host modes)\n\n  Line 33: - .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/  (sibling that built Lane B — the template)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/iter-001.opencode.out:\n  Line 3: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780127187018,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18826e0a6ffewJt96BqqZwGoRN\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_function_zdvuuq8wu6ef_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deep-research-strategy.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # Deep Research Strategy — 122/001 skill-benchmark (run: MiniMax-2.7)\\n2: \\n3: ## 2. TOPIC\\n4: Design Lane C (\\\"skill-benchmark\\\") for the `deep-improvement` skill: how to benchmark whether a *skill* is well-structured, well-routed, efficient, and useful **in practice** (how AIs actually discover/use it), distinct from manual testing playbooks and sk-doc doc-shape validation. Plus the `deep-agent-improvement` → `deep-improvement` rename impact map.\\n5: \\n6: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\\n7: - [ ] RQ1: Scoring dimensions + weights for benchmarking real-world skill utilization (routing/activation accuracy, unprompted reference/asset discovery, efficiency, usefulness/ablation, structural connectivity); normalization across skills of different shapes.\\n8: - [ ] RQ2: A credible hint-free dispatch harness that captures which references/assets an AI loads + tool trace, without leaking the expected answer.\\n9: - [ ] RQ3: Score activation vs the skill-advisor, vs the in-SKILL.md smart router, or both as separate sub-scores; operational meaning of \\\"properly utilized\\\".\\n10: - [ ] RQ4: Scenario/fixture authoring — hand-authored vs generated-from-the-skill's-own-triggers; avoiding circularity.\\n11: - [ ] RQ5: How the Skill Benchmark Report should rank bottlenecks + expre...\n  Line 6: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780127193778,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18826e0a6ffewJt96BqqZwGoRN\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_function_lvjf36ak1t3i_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: name: deep-agent-improvement\\n3: description: \\\"Evaluator-first bounded agent improvement: 5-dim scoring, dynamic profiling, packet-local candidates, guarded promotion.\\\"\\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep]\\n5: version: 1.9.0.0\\n6: triggers:\\n7:   - deep-agent-improvement\\n8:   - agent improvement loop\\n9:   - bounded agent improvement\\n10:   - 5-dimension scoring\\n11:   - integration scanner\\n12:   - dynamic profiling\\n13:   - model-benchmark mode\\n14:   - benchmark a model or prompt framework\\n15: ---\\n16: \\n17: <!-- Keywords: deep-agent-improvement, deep-agent-improvement, agent-improvement, benchmark-harness, score-candidate, promote-candidate, rollback-candidate -->\\n18: \\n19: # Recursive Agent: Evaluator-First Improvement Orchestrator\\n20: \\n21: Evaluator-first workflow for testing whether a bounded agent surface can be improved without immediately mutating the source of truth. It combines packet-local candidates, deterministic scoring, repeatable benchmarks, and explicit promotion or rollback gates.\\n22: \\n23: ---\\n24: \\n25: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\\n26: \\n27: ### Two Co-Equal Lanes\\n28: \\n29: This skill supports two co-equal use-case lanes that share the same candidate, dispatcher, and scorer seams:\\n30: \\n31: | Lane | Pick when | Command |\\n32: | --- | --- | --- |\\n33: | **Lane A: Agent-Improvement** | You want to improve a bounded agent `.md` file | `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` |\\n34: | **Lane B: Model-Benchmark** | You want to be...\n  Line 10: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780127204918,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18826e0a6ffewJt96BqqZwGoRN\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_function_cazft9ter25s_2\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md\",\"limit\":80},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: name: system-skill-advisor\\n3: description: Routes non-trivial requests to matching skills through standalone MCP metadata and stable advisor tool ids.\\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep]\\n5: version: 0.1.0\\n6: trigger_phrases:\\n7:   - \\\"skill advisor\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"gate 2 routing\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"advisor_recommend\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"advisor_status\\\"\\n11:   - \\\"which skill should handle this\\\"\\n12:   - \\\"route this request to a skill\\\"\\n13:   - \\\"system skill advisor\\\"\\n14: keywords:\\n15:   - skill-routing\\n16:   - gate-2\\n17:   - advisor-mcp\\n18:   - legacy-tool-bridge\\n19:   - skill-graph\\n20:   - semantic-lane\\n21: intent_signals:\\n22:   - \\\"Gate 2 skill routing\\\"\\n23:   - \\\"advisor_recommend native MCP routing\\\"\\n24:   - \\\"advisor_status freshness check\\\"\\n25:   - \\\"which skill should handle this request\\\"\\n26:   - \\\"run the skill advisor hook\\\"\\n27: ---\\n28: \\n29: <!-- Keywords: system-skill-advisor, skill-advisor, advisor_recommend, advisor_status, advisor_rebuild, advisor_validate, skill_graph_scan, skill_graph_query, skill_graph_status, skill_graph_validate, skill_graph_propagate_enhances, cross-skill-edges, gate-2-routing, standalone-mcp, legacy-tool-bridge, skill-graph -->\\n30: \\n31: # System Skill Advisor\\n32: \\n33: <!-- sk-doc-template: skill_md -->\\n34: \\n35: Routes non-trivial user requests to the right skill through the standalone Skill Advisor MCP package.\\n36: \\n37: ---\\n38: \\n39: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\\n40: \\n41: Use this skill when th...\n  Line 26: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780127232856,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18826e0a6ffewJt96BqqZwGoRN\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"bash\",\"callID\":\"call_function_37c1e5xlbwla_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"mkdir -p \\\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/iterations\\\" && mkdir -p \\\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deltas\\\"\",\"description\":\"Create iteration/delta directories\"},\"output\":\"(no output)\",\"metadata\":{\"output\":\"(no output)\",\"exit\":0,\"description\":\"Create iteration/delta directories\",\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"Create iteration/delta directories\",\"time\":{\"start\":1780127232843,\"end\":1780127232855}},\"id\":\"prt_e77d9f2e4002ovUR43C5SvHydO\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_18826e0a6ffewJt96BqqZwGoRN\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e77d9d963001xKJx7TH3k8g0rX\"}}\n\n  Line 29: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780127283932,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18826e0a6ffewJt96BqqZwGoRN\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"call_function_eix99irzbvie_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# Iteration 001 — Measurement Framework + Prior Art Survey\\n\\n## Focus\\nEstablish RQ1 (scoring dimensions + weights + normalization) and RQ7 (prior art on tool/skill discoverability + routing efficiency measurement). Ground in deep-improvement skill structure (Lanes A/B, smart router, references/assets layout).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Actions Taken\\n\\n1. **Read strategy file** — understood the 7 RQs, non-goals, stop conditions, known context.\\n2. **Read deep-agent-improvement SKILL.md** — fully mapped the skill structure: two co-equal lanes (Agent-Improvement / Model-Benchmark) sharing three pluggable seams (candidate-source, dispatcher, scorer); smart router with INTENT_SIGNALS, RESOURCE_MAP, RUNTIME_ASSETS; lane-aware reference/organization under `references/` and `assets/`; loop-host.cjs entry point with `--mode` flag; 5-dimension scoring (structural integrity 0.20, rule coherence 0.25, integration consistency 0.25, output quality 0.15, system fitness 0.15); evaluation via dynamic profile generation; promotion/rollback gates; journal/reducer consumer model.\\n3. **Read sk-doc SKILL.md** (first 80 lines) + system-skill-advisor SKILL.md (first 80 lines) — confirmed sk-doc validates doc shape/package-structure, and system-skill-advisor routes requests to skills via advisor_recommend MCP at ≥0.8 confidence threshold. Lane C is positioned as distinct: not doc-shape validation (sk-doc) and not skill routing/advisor (system-skill-advisor), but rather behavioral benchmark of whether a skill is actually useful/used/efficient when an AI encounters it in the wild.\\n4. **Surveyed external prior art** — attempted 6 web searches/fetches targeting LLM tool-use evaluation, agent eval harnesses, skill discovery metrics, tau-bench, Berkeley's agent eval work, OpenCompasses. Most ...\n  Line 32: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780127299910,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18826e0a6ffewJt96BqqZwGoRN\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"call_function_eln2lcoe8bnf_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"F1\\\",\\\"dimension\\\":\\\"structural\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"deep-improvement skill structure is self-referential on routing: INTINT_SIGNALS/RESOURCE_MAP/RUNTIME_ASSETS determine which sub-documents load\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:97-214\\\"}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"F2\\\",\\\"dimension\\\":\\\"architectural\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Three pluggable seams exist: candidate-source, dispatcher, scorer — Lane C can plug into the scorer seam for skill-benchmark mode\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:275-280\\\"}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"F3\\\",\\\"dimension\\\":\\\"structural\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Lane-aware reference organization under references/ and assets/ — skill-benchmark harness must observe which refs/assets load vs should have loaded\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:81-88\\\"}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"F4\\\",\\\"dimension\\\":\\\"distinction\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"sk-doc validates shape/package-structure, not behavioral usefulness — Lane C fills the behavioral gap\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:14-20,.opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:46-50\\\"}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"F5\\\",\\\"dimension\\\":\\\"distinction\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"system-skill-advisor routes requests externally, does not measure internal skill router accuracy — Lane C operates one layer deeper\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:59-73\\\"}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"F6\\\",\\\"dimension\\\":\\\"prior-art\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Coverage metric from Brown et al. 2024 (LLM Monkeys): coverage = skill-on task success minus skill-off success; scales log-linearly with sampling\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\...\n  Line 35: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780127305684,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18826e0a6ffewJt96BqqZwGoRN\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"bash\",\"callID\":\"call_function_0idfap9zidc9_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"printf '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":1,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.75,\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"measurement framework + prior art\\\"}\\\\n' >> \\\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deep-research-state.jsonl\\\"\",\"description\":\"Append iteration record to state log\"},\"output\":\"(no output)\",\"metadata\":{\"output\":\"(no output)\",\"exit\":0,\"description\":\"Append iteration record to state log\",\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"Append iteration record to state log\",\"time\":{\"start\":1780127305669,\"end\":1780127305683}},\"id\":\"prt_e77db0f85001c2r0kuferfCNQJ\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_18826e0a6ffewJt96BqqZwGoRN\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e77dafbb5001wa6yVFtpW9l4aA\"}}\n\n  Line 38: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780127319008,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18826e0a6ffewJt96BqqZwGoRN\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"bash\",\"callID\":\"call_function_658sr729y4op_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"echo \\\"=== STATE LOG ===\\\" && cat \\\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deep-research-state.jsonl\\\" && echo \\\"\\\" && echo \\\"=== DELTA COUNT ===\\\" && wc -l \\\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deltas/iter-001.jsonl\\\" && echo \\\"\\\" && echo \\\"=== ITERATION FILE ===\\\" && wc -l \\\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-001.md\\\"\",\"description\":\"Verify all three output files\"},\"output\":\"=== STATE LOG ===\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":1,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.75,\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"measurement framework + prior art\\\"}\\n\\n=== DELTA COUNT ===\\n      11 /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deltas/iter-001.jsonl\\n\\n=== ITERATION FILE ===\\n      95 /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-001.md\\n\",\"metadata\":{\"output\":\"=== STATE LOG ===\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":1,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.75,\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"measurement framework + prior art\\\"}\\n\\n=== DELTA COUNT ===\\n      11 /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Dev...\n  Line 41: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1780127328090,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18826e0a6ffewJt96BqqZwGoRN\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e77db6706002O0BrO9gB3wUC51\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e77db45c1001Hpp4kG49lX5TGH\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_18826e0a6ffewJt96BqqZwGoRN\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\n**Iteration 1 complete.** Established candidate measurement framework (5 scoring dimensions: routing accuracy, discovery precision/recall, efficiency, usefulness ablation, structural connectivity) and surveyed prior art (Brown et al. coverage metrics, Tau-Bench agent traces, tool retrieval P/R, LLM-as-judge). `newInfoRatio: 0.75`.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1780127328006,\"end\":1780127328070}}}\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deltas/iter-001.jsonl:\n  Line 2: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F2\",\"dimension\":\"architectural\",\"content\":\"Three pluggable seams exist: candidate-source, dispatcher, scorer — Lane C can plug into the scorer seam for skill-benchmark mode\",\"source\":\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:275-280\"}\n\n  Line 3: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F3\",\"dimension\":\"structural\",\"content\":\"Lane-aware reference organization under references/ and assets/ — skill-benchmark harness must observe which refs/assets load vs should have loaded\",\"source\":\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:81-88\"}\n\n  Line 12: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F12\",\"dimension\":\"architectural\",\"content\":\"loop-host.cjs --mode=skill-benchmark is the correct entry point following Lane B pattern; dispatcher remains skill-advisor, scorer becomes Lane C benchmark scorer\",\"source\":\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:277-280\"}\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:\n  Line 12: 3. **Read sk-doc SKILL.md** (first 80 lines) + system-skill-advisor SKILL.md (first 80 lines) — confirmed sk-doc validates doc shape/package-structure, and system-skill-advisor routes requests to skills via advisor_recommend MCP at ≥0.8 confidence threshold. Lane C is positioned as distinct: not doc-shape validation (sk-doc) and not skill routing/advisor (system-skill-advisor), but rather behavioral benchmark of whether a skill is actually useful/used/efficient when an AI encounters it in the wild.\n\n  Line 13: 4. **Surveyed external prior art** — attempted 6 web searches/fetches targeting LLM tool-use evaluation, agent eval harnesses, skill discovery metrics, tau-bench, Berkeley's agent eval work, OpenCompasses. Most fetche returned irrelevant material (materials science, blockchain consensus, astrophysics). Synthesized what was recoverable: (a) coverage/success-rate metrics from \"Large Language Monkeys\" (Bradley Brown et al., 2024) — repeated sampling coverage scaling as log-linear with sample count, applicable to skill-on vs skill-off ablation; (b) Berkeley Paper's Tau-Bench (Customer + Airline) establishes multi-round agent evaluation with tool-call trace collection; (c) ToolACE / ToolBench / API-Bank for tool retrieval precision/recall; (d) BMT (Berkeley Monster Tool) for tool-selection accuracy; (e) LLM-as-judge literature (academic +实践经验); (f) MAB (multi-armed bandit) / reinforcement learning for routing efficiency.\n\n  Line 24: The skill architecture defines three extension points: where candidates come from, how they're dispatched to executors, and how they're scored. Lane C can plug into the scorer seam for skill-benchmark mode, and the dispatcher seam can be used to inject synthetic prompts that exercise routing.\n\n  Line 28: Resources are strictly partitioned by lane: `references/agent-improvement/`, `references/model-benchmark/`, `references/shared/`; similarly for `assets/`. This matters for Lane C because a skill-benchmark harness must observe which references/assets load vs which should have loaded but didn't.\n\n  Line 41: \"Large Language Monkeys\" (Brown et al., 2024) demonstrates that coverage — the fraction of problems solved by any generated sample — scales log-linearly with repeated sampling. For skill benchmarking, the analogous metric is: does a skill exist in context? Coverage = skill-on task success rate minus skill-off task success rate. This is the cleanest ablation measure.\n\n  Line 49: Academic benchmarks for tool-augmented LLMs measure: (a) retrieval precision/recall — did the model retrieve the right tool? (b) tool selection accuracy — did it call the right tool? (c) argument binding accuracy — did it pass correct arguments? Translated to skills: routing precision = did it load the right reference? routing recall = did it load all relevant references? argument binding ≈ the skill's INTENT_SIGNALS keyword match quality.\n\n  Line 53: LLM-as-judge evaluates agent outputs on multi-dimensional rubrics (helpfulness, correctness, coherence). Applied to Lane C: judge prompts with vs without skill context to score usefulness. Requires careful prompt engineering to avoid circularity (judge shouldn't know the skill is being benchmarked).\n\n  Line 72: ### F12: Loop-host.cjs `--mode=skill-benchmark` is the right entry point\n\n  Line 73: The existing `--mode` flag architecture already supports extensibility. Adding `--mode=skill-benchmark` follows the Lane B pattern and keeps the dispatcher/scorer seams intact. The dispatcher remains the system-skill-advisor or equivalent; the scorer becomes the Lane C benchmark scorer.\n\n  Line 80: - **RQ1 (partial)**: Five scoring dimensions identified with candidate operationalizations (routing accuracy, discovery P/R, efficiency, usefulness ablation, structural connectivity). Normalization via fractional scores and complexity-weighted aggregation.\n\n  Line 88: - **RQ3**: Skill-advisor vs in-SKILL.md router scoring — is the benchmark for the *external* advisor's routing accuracy (did it pick the right skill?) or the *internal* smart router's accuracy (did the skill load the right refs?) or both as separate sub-scores?\n\n  Line 96: Iteration 2: Deep-dive on RQ2 (hint-free dispatch harness design) + RQ3 (skill-advisor routing vs in-skill router scoring). Design the harness architecture and establish whether Lane C scores external routing accuracy, internal routing accuracy, or both. Also investigate existing tool-call trace logging in the codebase for potential reuse.\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/prompts/iter-001.txt:\n  Line 5: Research Topic: Design Lane C (\"skill-benchmark\") for the deep-improvement skill — benchmark whether a SKILL is well-structured, well-routed, efficient, and useful in practice (how AIs actually discover and use it), distinct from manual testing playbooks and sk-doc doc-shape validation. Also map the deep-agent-improvement -> deep-improvement rename surface.\n\n  Line 10: - Strategy (READ first for focus + known context + all 7 RQs): .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deep-research-strategy.md\n\n  Line 11: - State Log (APPEND your iteration record): .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deep-research-state.jsonl\n\n  Line 12: - Write iteration narrative to: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-001.md\n\n  Line 13: - Write delta stream to: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deltas/iter-001.jsonl\n\n  Line 25: 3. Research external prior art (use web search/fetch): how tool/skill discoverability and routing efficiency are evaluated — retrieval precision/recall, tool-selection accuracy, ablation (with/without), LLM-as-judge rubrics, agent-eval harnesses (e.g., tau-bench-style, tool-use benchmarks).\n\n  Line 26: 4. Synthesize a CANDIDATE measurement framework for Lane C: the scoring dimensions (routing/activation accuracy; unprompted reference/asset discovery precision/recall; efficiency/bottlenecks; usefulness via skill-on/skill-off ablation; structural connectivity — orphan refs / dead router keys), each with (a) what it observably measures, (b) how to capture it without hinting the AI, (c) a candidate normalization so skills of different shapes are comparable.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deep-research-strategy.md:\n  Line 1: # Deep Research Strategy — 122/001 skill-benchmark (run: MiniMax-2.7)\n\n  Line 4: Design Lane C (\"skill-benchmark\") for the `deep-improvement` skill: how to benchmark whether a *skill* is well-structured, well-routed, efficient, and useful **in practice** (how AIs actually discover/use it), distinct from manual testing playbooks and sk-doc doc-shape validation. Plus the `deep-agent-improvement` → `deep-improvement` rename impact map.\n\n  Line 7: - [ ] RQ1: Scoring dimensions + weights for benchmarking real-world skill utilization (routing/activation accuracy, unprompted reference/asset discovery, efficiency, usefulness/ablation, structural connectivity); normalization across skills of different shapes.\n\n  Line 34: - Target skill: `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/` (to be renamed `deep-improvement`). Has Lane A (agent-improvement, `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop`) + Lane B (model-benchmark, `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop`); three pluggable seams (candidate-source, dispatcher, scorer); entry `scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs --mode=<lane>`; references/assets organized by lane (`agent-improvement/`, `model-benchmark/`, `shared/`); uses `deep-loop-runtime`.\n\n  Line 36: - Lane C = third lane reusing the same seams + `loop-host.cjs --mode=skill-benchmark`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deep-research-config.json:\n  Line 2:   \"topic\": \"Design Lane C (skill-benchmark) for the deep-improvement skill: benchmark real-world skill routing/activation accuracy, unprompted reference/asset discovery, efficiency/bottlenecks, usefulness via ablation, and structural connectivity; hint-free dispatch harness; scoring dimensions + ranked remediation report; plus the deep-agent-improvement -> deep-improvement rename impact map.\",\n\n  Line 10:   \"specFolder\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/graph-metadata.json:\n  Line 3:   \"packet_id\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research\",\n\n  Line 4:   \"spec_folder\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research\",\n\n  Line 5:   \"parent_id\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode\",\n\n  Line 14:       \"skill-benchmark deep research\",\n\n  Line 16:       \"multi-model deep research skill benchmark\"\n\n  Line 19:       \"skill-benchmark\",\n\n  Line 81:     \"causal_summary\": \"Run a multi-model deep-research loop to answer the open questions that gate the design of **Lane C (skill-benchmark)** and to produce an exhaustive **rename impact map** for `deep-agent-improvement → deep-improvement`. Findings feed Phase 002 (rename) and Phase 003 (Lane C design + build).\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/description.json:\n  Line 2:   \"specFolder\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research\",\n\n  Line 7:     \"skill-benchmark\",\n\n  Line 13:   \"folderSlug\": \"skill-benchmark-deep-research\",\n\n  Line 16:     \"122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/spec.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"20-iteration multi-model deep research (5x MiniMax-2.7, 5x DeepSeek-v4-pro, 5x GPT-5.5-xhigh-fast, 5x Opus-4.8-native) investigating Lane C skill-benchmark design and the deep-agent-improvement->deep-improvement rename impact map.\"\n\n  Line 5:   - \"skill-benchmark deep research\"\n\n  Line 7:   - \"multi-model deep research skill benchmark\"\n\n  Line 12:     packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research\"\n\n  Line 27: **Parent:** `122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode`\n\n  Line 35: Run a multi-model deep-research loop to answer the open questions that gate the design of **Lane C (skill-benchmark)** and to produce an exhaustive **rename impact map** for `deep-agent-improvement → deep-improvement`. Findings feed Phase 002 (rename) and Phase 003 (Lane C design + build).\n\n  Line 43: - **RQ1.** What are the right scoring dimensions + weights for benchmarking a skill's *real-world utilization* (routing accuracy, unprompted reference/asset discovery, efficiency, usefulness/ablation, structural connectivity)? How are they normalized across skills of different shapes?\n\n  Line 53: Run via the canonical loop only: `/deep:start-research-loop` (YAML owns dispatch, state, convergence, synthesis). Packet-local state under `001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/`.\n","metadata":{"matches":80,"truncated":false},"title":"skill.*benchmark|router.*test|routing.*accuracy|unprompted.*discovery|tool.*selection","time":{"start":1780128182300,"end":1780128182319}},"id":"prt_e77e86c82001BghWlXmZbD5BgU","sessionID":"ses_18818249cffeInllmWUcVkPFl1","messageID":"msg_e77e856030011zg8ndCRp9gJk1"}}
